ce Academy, Ankara, Turkey. . IN-SERVICE TRAINING RECEIVED: 2012 Situation Training. Turkish National Police Organization, Antalya Turkey. 2007 (02-29 April) Mid-Level Police Management. Turkish National Police Academy, Ankara, Turkey. 2005 Graduate Preparation Course (GPS) for 2 months, University of North Texas, Denton, Texas, USA.         English course at the Intensive English Language Institute (IELI), University of North Texas, Denton, Texas, USA. 2001 Terror, Organized Crime, & Human Rights.  Turkish National Police Organization, Ankara, Turkey. 2001 The Europe Union. Turkish National Police Organization, Ankara, Turkey. 2000 New Training Strategies in the Training & Education of Police Students. Police Academy, Kiev, Ukraine. 1997 Self-Defense. Turkish National Police Academy, Ankara, Turkey. 1998 Firearms. Turkish National Police Academy, Ankara, Turkey. 1996 Police Students\u2019 Physiology. Turkish National Police Academy, Ankara, Turkey. 1988-1989 German language course for 9 months. Adana, Turkey. IN-SERVICE TRAINING DELIVERED: 2010 (November-December) Police Ethics. Police Department, Bitlis, Turkey. 2010 (19-22 April) Trainers of Police Ethics. Antalya, Turkey. 2010 (18-19 March) Police Administration & Police Ethics. Presentation title: \u201cMechanisms Controlling Bureaucracy and Police Ethics as a Control Mechanism\u201d           with the support of the Europe Union. Antalya, Turkey. CLASSES TAUGHT: Spring 2013 Democratic Theory, Afyon Kocatepe University, Department of Public Administration (undergraduate English language course for 49 students). Spring 2013 Introduction to Politics-II, Afyon Kocatepe University, Department of Public Administration (undergraduate level course delivered to 81 students). Spring 2013 Transformation of the Society and Modernization in Turkey, Afyon Kocatepe University, Dept. of Public Administration (undergraduate course for 99 students). Spring 2013 Criminal Procedure Law, Afyonkarahisar Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered to 150 students). Fall 2012 Introduction to Politics-I, Afyon Kocatepe University, Department of Public Administration (undergraduate level course delivered to 70 students). Fall 2012 Bureaucracy, Afyon Kocatepe University, Department of Public Administration (undergraduate level course delivered to 100 students). Fall 2012 Contemporary Political Systems, Afyon Kocatepe University, Dept. of Public Administration (undergraduate English language course for 50 students). Fall 2012 Turkish Constitution, Afyonkarahisar Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered to 150 students).   Fall 2012 Police Vocational English, Afyonkarahisar Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered to 80 students). Spring 2012 Public Relations and Communication, Bitlis Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered to 300 students). Fall 2011 Turkish Constitution, Bitlis Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered to 200 students). Spring 2011 Police Ethics, Bitlis Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered 300 students). Fall 2010 Turkish Constitution and the Organizational Structure of the Turkish Government, Bitlis Police Academy (associate degree course for 300 students). Spring 2010 Police Ethics, Bitlis Police Academy (associate degree level course delivered to 300 students). WORK EXPERIENCE: September 2012-present: Full-time lecturer and researcher, Afyonkarahisar Police Academy. January 2010-August 2012: Instructor and Training Division Manager, Bitlis Police Academy. January 2005-January 2010: Graduate program at University of North Texas, Denton, Texas, USA. May 17-30, 2006: The Community Service Project in Matzlamia, Jalisco, Mexico (UNT study abroad program).   September 2005-May 2006: Research Assistant at Turkish Institute for Police Studies (TIPS), University of North Texas, Denton, Texas, USA. June 14, 2004-December 24, 2004: Bitlis City Police Department in Turkey. June 14-July 22, 2004: Chief of Admin Office, Human Resources Division-Police Dept., July 22-December 24, 2004: police station commander. December 2003-May 2004: Mandatory military service, the 6th Turkish Air Force Base, Balikesir, Turkey. October 2002-October 2003: United Nations Mission in Kosovo (UNMIK), Civilian Police Officer (peacekeeper). October 2002-February 2003: Patrol officer-North Police Station, Prishtina, Kosovo; February 2003-October 2003: Operations Officer-North Police Station, Prishtina, Kosovo. 1996\u20132002: Chief of Admin Office, Division of Lecturers at the Turkish National Police Academy (TNPA), Ankara, Turkey. Safety Supervisor at shooting range, TNPA for undergraduate police students; assistant to shooting instructors. 2000-2001: Instructor for computer course at the TNPA for undergraduate police students for three terms. Taught office programs such as word, excel, PowerPoint programs to about 500 police students). PUBLICATIONS (in peer-reviewed journals and book chapters before doctoral degree):Ulkemen, S. (2008). FBI personel politikalar\u0131 ve Türk polis teskilatina oneriler (FBI Personnel Policies and the Recommendations to the Turkish National Police Organization),       Turkish Journal of Police Studies 10(2), 25-50.Ulkemen, S., Akdogan, H., Kapti, A., and Gultekin, S. (2008). Meksika Polis Te\u015fkilat\u0131 (The Law Enforcement Agencies of Mexico), in H.H. Cevik (Ed.) Kar\u015f\u0131la\u015ft\u0131rmal\u0131 polis yönetimi        (Comparative Police Administration and Management). Ankara: A Publication of Turkish National Police Organization.Demirci, S. and Ulkemen S. (2005). The U.S. Government and Law Enforcement Agencies. Turkish Journal of Police Studies 7(3), 59-97.  PUBLICATIONS (in peer-reviewed journals and book chapters) (after doctoral degree): Tasdoven, H. and Ulkemen, S. (Coming soon, 2013). Insan kaynaklar\u0131 yönetiminde yetkinliklere dayal\u0131 e\u011fitim sistemi: Polis egitiminin temel sorunlar\u0131na cözüm arayisi. (Competency Based